    pearls: ["Steady state is reached after 4-5 half-lives regardless of dose, route, or dosing interval — this applies to both drug accumulation and washout","A loading dose achieves immediate therapeutic levels but does NOT change the time to steady state — maintenance dosing still takes 4-5 half-lives to stabilize","Phenytoin follows zero-order kinetics at therapeutic doses — small dose increases can cause disproportionately large rises in plasma concentration leading to toxicity","For drugs with narrow therapeutic indices (digoxin, lithium, aminoglycosides, warfarin), always verify drug levels and renal function before dose adjustments","When a CYP450 inhibitor is added (e.g., fluconazole inhibiting CYP3A4), the interacting drug reaches a new higher steady state after 4-5 half-lives of the affected drug"],
